## Important Rules

- **ADRs are immutable.** Once Accepted, edit only the Status field on supersession. Never rewrite history.
- **Negative consequences are mandatory.** A decision with no downside was not honestly reviewed.
- **Number, never rename.** File numbers are part of the URL. If you rename, you break every external reference.
- **One decision per ADR.** Splitting is cheap; bundling is expensive.
- **Present tense imperative for titles.** "Use Postgres" not "Postgres should be used" not "We decided on Postgres."
- **Lint is read-only.** Report findings, recommend fixes, do not auto-edit ADR files.
